## Idea

A _Heisenberg $n$-group_ is a sub-[[âˆž-group]] of a [[quantomorphism n-group]] on those whose underlying [[n-plectomorphisms]] act "linearly" in a prescribed way. This is the higher refinement of the traditional notion of _[[Heisenberg group]]_.

## Definition

For $(X, \omega)$ an [[n-plectic geometry]] with [[higher geometric quantization|higher geometric prequantization]] $(X, \nabla)$ and for $X$ equipped with the [[âˆž-action]] of an [[abelian âˆž-group]]m the corresponding _Heisenberg n-group_ is the sub-[[âˆž-group]] of the [[quantomorphism n-group]] on those elements whose corresponding [[n-plectomorphism]] is given by such a linear action.

The corresponding [[Lie n-algebra]] is the _[[Heisenberg Lie n-algebra]]_.


